text: Raymond Eric Cann (born 13 December 1937) is a male former diver who competed for England. ==Diving career== He represented Great Britain in the Diving at the 1956 Summer Olympics. He represented England and won a bronze medal in the 10 metres platform at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1937 births Category:Living people Category:English male divers Category:Olympic divers of Great Britain Category:Divers at the 1956 Summer Olympics Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in diving Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England Category:Divers at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games
